        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Beastlords quest weapons are claws that use the "Hand to Hand" skill. They aren't allowed to use most weapons except for a few small 1h slashers and many piercers. They get the monks Safe fall at skill 50 (Won't raise from there) and later in life they get the monks "Block" ability. That's where the similarities between Beastlords and Monks ends.</P><P>They were described as Shaman/Warrior hybrids. But there's definately some Monk thrown into the mix.</P><P>If their pets aren't allowed on raids, that's where I fear the Beastlords will suffer greatly. They can't tank and won't have the raw Melee output of the Warriors/Rogues/Rangers.</P><P>It'll be interesting to see some Beastlords on raids soon, to start to define their roles and abilities.</P><P><BR><img src="http://neogravity.homestead.com/files/gojirax.jpg" border="0"><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
